## Traps

- **The Ledger is int-only.** `envoy.ledger.canonical.canonical_dumps` rejects floats — caught one in this session when `threshold_pct: float` in the budget_threshold_crossed payload raised. Fix: encode as integer basis points (`threshold_bps`, 0.80 → 8000). Any new ledger entry type with a fractional field MUST do the same.
- **`EnvoyLedger.verify_chain()` and `EnvoyLedger.query()` are BOTH `async def`**, despite the inspect.signature stub showing only `-> VerificationReport` / `-> list[EntryEnvelope]`. Pyright catches the missing `await` — don't trust the apparent sync signature, run pyright/await.
- **Threshold callbacks fire OUTSIDE the upstream `BudgetTracker._lock` but on the calling thread.** The dispatcher's `enqueue` (sync `put_nowait`) is the ONLY work allowed on that thread. The async Grant-Moment wiring runs in the dispatcher worker, off the callback thread — re-entrancy safe. `_arm_thresholds` excludes `per_call` (the anomaly detector owns single-call magnitude; arming per_call would fire on every substantial call).
- **The double-billing guard is timed BEFORE mutation** (record-intent-first) in `record_for_call` — both expiry and success branches set `_recorded_reservations` before `_rollback`/record-loop. This is the dual defense (no double-CHARGE AND no double-RELEASE). Don't move it back to "after success" without breaking HIGH#1.
- **Anomaly detector dominates small-budget tests.** The single-call >50%-of-session-remaining detector fires aggressively when `per_session` is small. For tests of OTHER behaviors, inject `no_op_anomaly_detector()` from `tests/helpers/budget_harness.py` (uses unreachable `1e18` threshold).
- **`budget_velocity_check` is now reserved-aware** (commit 53135ab, M2 fix). Uses `EnvoyBudgetOrchestrator.window_check` (per-window `BudgetCheckResult`) — `committed + reserved >= allocated` is the breach predicate.
- **freezegun is still NOT in `.venv`** — the budget tests use a `_Clock()` helper class (mutable `.now`), same pattern as daily_digest's `_utc_now()` seam.
- **pyright duck-typing noise persists**: `Import "envoy.budget.*" could not be resolved` on the new package files is stale (runtime imports work + 1580 tests pass). ruff IS the lint of record here.

